### Service Registry — Dashboard & Registration Endpoints
### Read endpoints go through the API gateway (port 8080) per AGENTS.md
### Registration/heartbeat/deregister are internal (service-to-service on port 3075)

### List all registered services (via gateway — requires admin auth)
GET http://localhost:8080/v1/registry/services
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Get instances of a specific service (via gateway — requires admin auth)
GET http://localhost:8080/v1/registry/services/core-service
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### --- Internal endpoints (service-to-service, not through gateway) ---

### Manually register a service (internal)
POST http://localhost:3075/v1/registry/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "test-service",
  "version": "0.1.0",
  "host": "localhost",
  "port": 9999
}

###

### Send heartbeat (internal)
PUT http://localhost:3075/v1/registry/heartbeat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "test-service",
  "port": 9999
}

###

### Deregister a service (internal)
DELETE http://localhost:3075/v1/registry/deregister
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "test-service",
  "port": 9999
}

###

### Health check (internal — not proxied)
GET http://localhost:3075/health

###

### Readiness check (internal — not proxied)
GET http://localhost:3075/ready

###

### Swagger docs (internal — not proxied)
GET http://localhost:3075/docs
